{
  "name": "Organ Change Detector",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Detects edits to body organ files and checks for cross-organ coherence.",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": ["**/shared/context/body/*.md"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A body organ file was edited. Check: 1) Does this edit conflict with other organs? Flag any cross-organ inconsistencies. 2) If the edited file is heart.md or gut.md, verify the edit was made by the karpathy agent — these files are gated. If not by karpathy, flag the unauthorized edit. 3) Log the change to ~/shared/context/intake/organ-changes.md with timestamp, file name, and summary of change."
  }
}

### Common Pitfalls — preamble
- Misinterpreting this section causes downstream errors
- Always validate assumptions before acting on this data
- Cross-reference with related sections for completeness
